# Markdown Quality

When creating or editing Markdown files, always ensure they pass markdownlint with the project's `.markdownlint.json` config:

- Use ATX-style headings (`#`, `##`, etc.), never setext (underline) style.
- Use dashes (`-`) for unordered lists.
- No trailing punctuation in headings.
- Surround headings and lists with blank lines.
- No inline HTML unless absolutely necessary.
- End every file with a single newline.
- No trailing whitespace on any line.

If you notice any of these issues in a Markdown file you are editing, fix them before finishing.
